Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.78,0:00:02.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then this machine was-
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.53,0:00:05.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The demon we\Nsaw 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.12,0:00:10.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always figured it had been annihilated\Nin the damage of Heaven's Fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:12.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Capt. Magbaredge!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:17.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world... is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.89,0:00:26.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Confirm that the ship\Nis fitted out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.26,0:00:29.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Check its fuel, weapons,\Nand munitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.14,0:00:30.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.19,0:00:38.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deucalion. That's this ship's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.36,0:00:42.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you suppose such a\Nfine ship was abandoned
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.86,0:00:44.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,without ever sending it\Ninto battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.86,0:00:48.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reserves are still working! If we can\Nfeed it power, it'll be good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.62,0:00:51.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fuel level is...\NI'm not sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.16,0:00:52.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of report is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.83,0:00:55.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no fuel gauge!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.84,0:00:58.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.46,0:01:03.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why this ship\Nwas abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.09,0:01:06.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.10,0:01:08.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An Aldnoah drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.35,0:01:15.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, civilians aren't\Nallowed in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.27,0:01:16.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave imme-
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.81,0:01:17.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.90,0:01:20.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:26.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no cause for alarm.\NI am your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.50,0:01:34.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.01,0:01:50.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I command you in the name\Nof Asseylum Vers Allusia!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.35,0:01:53.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah, awaken!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.44,0:04:11.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Are we in a more\Ntalkative mood now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:15.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is your objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.99,0:04:18.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To what end did you\Ngo to that island?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.38,0:04:34.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perhaps he has had enough,\NCount Cruhteo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.81,0:04:42.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We needn't show pity to a member\Nof a lower race, Count Saazbaum.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.94,0:04:45.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he dies, we learn nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.48,0:04:49.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He sought an audience with the emperor,\Nheedless of the risk to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.41,0:04:50.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:52.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would know his intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.82,0:04:54.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Intent?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.70,0:04:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As if this child\Nis capable of thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.41,0:05:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Milord Cruhteo. We have\Nlocated the wreckage{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.08,0:05:03.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}of an Orbital Knight Kataphrakt\Non the island.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.21,0:05:05.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.96,0:05:08.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We believe it to be that of\NCountess Femieanne's Hellas.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:09.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.05,0:05:12.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was Countess Femieanne slain by?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.26,0:05:17.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A waste of time, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.10,0:05:20.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Abide, Count Cruhteo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.56,0:05:28.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me now! If you do,\NI will put you out of your misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.78,0:05:35.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Continue to suffer, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.62,0:05:44.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.37,0:05:48.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deucalion... A flying battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:52.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nina, what makes it fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.34,0:05:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That Martian thing, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:55.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.55,0:05:56.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.68,0:06:01.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are the helm controls like a normal ship's?\NCan you handle this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.68,0:06:06.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The FCS has been adjusted so it\Nfeels the same when I steer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.81,0:06:09.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should you be away from\Nyour post, Calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:12.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big deal if I want\Nto look around a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.61,0:06:14.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, there's no\Nbigwigs around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.03,0:06:17.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Where's Inaho?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:21.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the bigwig's office.\NWith the Martians.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.83,0:06:22.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Martians...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.91,0:06:27.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Thanks to her, this ship's\NAldnoah drive is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.54,0:06:30.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.13,0:06:36.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Mars Knights plotted your assassination?\NI find that hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.47,0:06:42.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Capt. Magbaredge, if we disclosed this information,\Nperhaps the Mars Knights would stop attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.81,0:06:46.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our communications satellites and\Ntelecom bases have been wiped out,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:50.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and long-range transmissions are impossible\Nthanks to their jamming signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.27,0:06:52.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we're going to try to get the word\Nout that the princess is safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.94,0:06:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there's no guarantee that the proper\Nagencies would get the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.19,0:07:01.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You believe it would make us the target of\Nthe Mars Knights who plotted her death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.95,0:07:07.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our plan all along was to go to United\NEarth HQ in Russia to regroup, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.21,0:07:13.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Until we arrive, we will\Nsee to your safety, Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:14.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.88,0:07:17.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Kaizuka Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.26,0:07:19.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho Kaizuka, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.76,0:07:22.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet Areash.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:28.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You two were aware of this,\Nyet neglected to inform me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:32.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a soldier. I'm not\Nobligated to report to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.19,0:07:33.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Junior?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.82,0:07:37.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't neglect to inform you.\NI deliberately didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.69,0:07:40.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Watch what you say! You're putting\Nyourself on very thin ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.91,0:07:42.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I asked him not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.33,0:07:47.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someone working with the\Nassassins might be aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:48.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eddelrittuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.33,0:07:51.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't trust you Martians, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.17,0:07:57.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A nation that latched onto\Nan archaic feudal system
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.71,0:08:00.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that relies on the superscience of an\Nancient civilization called Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.05,0:08:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commoners who are obsessed with proving\N themselves in battle to win social standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:09.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And nobility who casually betray them\Nand grind them into the dirt...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.37,0:08:13.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can you possibly\Ntrust people like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.08,0:08:17.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't trust them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.69,0:08:20.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All Martians are the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.25,0:08:36.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how far science advances, these\Nprocedures always remain primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.63,0:08:41.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And at times... are all the\Nmore effective for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.80,0:08:46.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:51.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.23,0:08:54.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.19,0:08:57.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.65,0:09:05.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, has that loosened\Nyour tongue?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.03,0:09:10.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you... sworn loyalty...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.62,0:09:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to Princess Asseylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:19.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.38,0:09:20.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.59,0:09:25.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impudent boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.14,0:09:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And how are we feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.14,0:09:31.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lousy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:35.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to hear it. The medicine\Nseems to be working.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:38.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that coming here\Ntriggered a relapse...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:41.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd feel a lot better if\Nyou'd give me some booze.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:45.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the sort of medicine\Nyou pester your doctor for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.45,0:09:47.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hate this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:55.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Birds"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.87,0:09:56.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:09:59.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Animals that fly\Nthrough the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:02.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we reach Earth, I will be\Nable to see them, won't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.01,0:10:08.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Progress is slow, but the scars\Nof Heaven's Fall are fading.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.05,0:10:12.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nature is powerful, and when\Nan area is depopulated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:15.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it immediately begins\Nto reclaim it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.31,0:10:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Depopulated?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.19,0:10:20.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. As opposed\Nto urban areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.11,0:10:23.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,plant life reproduces abundantly\Nin devastated regions, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.32,0:10:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is sad, isn't it? That we are\Nunable to thrive together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.66,0:10:35.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all! With forethought\Nand hard work, it is possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.12,0:10:36.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.54,0:10:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It is possible for us\Nto thrive together!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.09,0:10:47.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Terran? Do you feel\Nlike talking now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.43,0:10:53.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count... Do you care for\Nthe princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.43,0:10:54.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.93,0:10:59.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you... her ally?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.35,0:11:01.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.94,0:11:03.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.61,0:11:05.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As punishment for your crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.92,0:11:09.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall give your compatriots on Earth\N a taste of even greater horrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.82,0:11:12.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it, you were lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.91,0:11:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want an excuse to go\Nto war with Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.13,0:11:26.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness wished for\Npeace with Earth, but you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.92,0:11:29.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are exploiting her death...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.43,0:11:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to crush her dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.15,0:11:45.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not invoke her memory\Nso lightly, you filthy Terran!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.91,0:11:57.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sey-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.66,0:12:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.58,0:12:03.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not mind you\Ncalling me Seylum, Inaho.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.21,0:12:04.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.50,0:12:07.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, add\N"Your Highness" to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.59,0:12:08.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eddeltittuo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.76,0:12:09.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But, Milady!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.67,0:12:13.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do apologize. This is her way\Nof looking out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.64,0:12:16.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.10,0:12:18.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I ran into someone\Non Tanegashima who-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.68,0:12:19.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inaho!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.94,0:12:25.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that there were\NMartians hiding among us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.19,0:12:26.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.90,0:12:30.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?!\NI'm gonna avenge Okojo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.82,0:12:34.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the Princess\Nof Mars you seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.41,0:12:36.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.79,0:12:41.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I deeply regret that so many of your fellow\NTerrans have been injured or killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.12,0:12:45.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I assure you, this war\Nis not what Vers wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.42,0:12:50.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am doing all I can to bring this meaningless\Nconflict to an end as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.26,0:12:54.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Sure.\NDo your best, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.72,0:12:56.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you blushing for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.55,0:12:57.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're as red as a lobster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.22,0:12:59.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you guys\Ncome from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.47,0:13:01.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say you were\Ngoing to get revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.52,0:13:04.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say something about\Nall Martians being the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.77,0:13:07.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never said any such thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.11,0:13:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are good Martians and bad\NMartians, same as everywhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.57,0:13:11.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Inaho?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.99,0:13:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Back my play, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.24,0:13:18.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I said, there's no\Ntrusting Terrans...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:27.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have saved me countless times\Nsince we arrived on Earth, Inaho.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.63,0:13:33.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't fighting for you\Nin particular, Seylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.22,0:13:39.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I was drafted. If I don't\Nfight, it puts me in danger, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:44.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, that does not change\Nthe fact that I owe you my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.27,0:13:45.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.11,0:13:52.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That Martian that I met on\NTanegashima was looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.28,0:13:57.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And he was scared that you\Nwere being exploited.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.62,0:13:58.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.28,0:14:03.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are some among the enemy\Nwho think that you are still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.50,0:14:06.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest staying\Non your guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.50,0:14:12.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.59,0:14:16.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A good luck charm given to me by a dear\NTerran friend when we arrived at Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.09,0:14:18.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By a Terran?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.05,0:14:23.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The son of a scientist who\Nvisited Mars to study Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.56,0:14:28.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard all manner of stories\Nregarding Earth from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.61,0:14:35.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About the sea.\NAbout the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:39.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About the creatures\Nwho live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.53,0:14:45.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I heard these stories, I grew\Nmore and more enamored of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.04,0:14:49.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, I wanted more than\Nanything to come to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.92,0:14:55.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I wished to establish\Npeaceful relations with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.31,0:15:09.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That creature,\Ncould that be... a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.69,0:15:12.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a black-tailed gull.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.90,0:15:17.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An animal that flies through the sky!\NThey really do exist, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.86,0:15:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is just as you said, Slaine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.50,0:15:39.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My life was saved by Princess\NAsseylum that day...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.39,0:15:47.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it weren't for her,\NI wouldn't be alive now...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.69,0:15:55.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So this time, I will\Nprotect you, Your Highness!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.11,0:16:01.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mustn't divulge that\Nshe is alive...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.61,0:16:07.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't let those who hope to exploit\Nthe princess have their way...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.08,0:16:11.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be they Martian...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:15.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...or Terran.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.88,0:16:19.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.19,0:16:35.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How regretful Princess\NAsseylum must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.65,0:16:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To put her faith in inferior scum like\Nhim and lose her life as a result...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.90,0:16:42.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Milord Cruhteo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.11,0:16:43.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:46.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We've discovered something on\Nthe island that we can't explain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.49,0:16:49.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wreckage of another Kataphrakt, one not\Nbelonging to Countess Femieanne.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.21,0:16:54.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the one that fell\Nto Earth 15 years ago...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Deucalion...!\NIt can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.75,0:16:59.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unit's Aldnoah drive\Nhad been removed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.84,0:17:03.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?! No, it is no\Ncause for concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.26,0:17:07.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They cannot activate\Nthe Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.89,0:17:14.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is so amusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.81,0:17:17.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.15,0:17:21.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this.\NKill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.53,0:17:24.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not yet, Count Cruhteo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:27.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He makes a mockery of the\Nproud Orbital Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.87,0:17:32.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will spread your ashes\Nhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.04,0:17:38.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, scum!\NWhat made you laugh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.63,0:17:40.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What made you laugh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.47,0:17:49.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me. Without Aldnoah, the Terrans could\Nnot have been the ones who slew Hellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:17:55.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is your punishment for what you've\Ndone to Her Highness' beloved Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.48,0:17:59.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Preposterous. They have no one\Ncapable of activating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.07,0:18:02.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only a handful of Versians\Nhave come down to Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.03,0:18:06.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and the only ones possessing\Nthe right of activation are...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.16,0:18:07.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It cannot be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.58,0:18:17.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum?!\NIs the princess still alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.25,0:18:21.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Speak! Is she unharmed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.96,0:18:23.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.14,0:18:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If she were...\NWhat would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:37.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assassinate her again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.40,0:18:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.73,0:18:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was it not you who gave Sir Trillram\Nhis orders? To kill the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.99,0:18:46.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You dare suggest I-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.28,0:18:51.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"If we let her live, my entire clan and its\Nfollowers will be branded as traitors."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.91,0:18:57.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you... You claimed to have\Nseen his death, as I recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.92,0:19:00.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I shot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.67,0:19:05.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then he did not get caught\Nin the meteor bombardment...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.76,0:19:10.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the Nilokeras, with its\Ndimensional barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.10,0:19:15.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you have your way...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.60,0:19:23.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness... will\Nsmash your plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.57,0:19:34.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum... is alive?\NThat is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.79,0:19:37.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.25,0:19:42.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You learned the truth and went out in\Nsearch of the princess on your own?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:47.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Telling no one, for fear\Nof alerting the traitors...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.09,0:19:48.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Alone, without support...!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.18,0:19:53.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Willing to risk being captured\Nand killed by us...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.98,0:20:01.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.27,0:20:04.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have proven your loyalty\Na thousand times over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.98,0:20:06.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See to this man's injuries!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.90,0:20:07.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.74,0:20:13.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I, too, swore loyalty\Nto Her Highness...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.66,0:20:18.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those traitors who dared to lay\Na hand on her Highness will pay!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.42,0:20:22.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Put me through to\NUnited Earth Headquarters!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.92,0:20:27.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Offer a cease-fire and request their\Nassistance in locating the princess!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.55,0:20:32.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We will identify those who made a mockery\Nof the Orbital Knights and punish them!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.97,0:20:37.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Cruhteo! An object\Nis approaching from orbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.31,0:20:39.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What? Another meteor bombardment?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.73,0:20:40.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, Milord!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:43.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Given its rate of deceleration,\Nit is far less dense!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:47.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is adjusting its entry trajectory.\NEstimated landing point is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.24,0:20:50.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...this Landing Castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.54,0:21:03.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.21,0:21:11.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's... the Dioscuria!\NCount Saazbaum?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.69,0:21:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see... It is all clear now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.19,0:21:34.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The mastermind of\Nthe assassination plot was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.11,0:21:35.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ready my Tharsis!
